This is an extension to the Firefox add-on Operator adding support 
for citations of classical primary sources encoded using a customised microformat and CTS URNs.

This version of the extension is synchronised with the encoding pattern #2 described at <http://wiki.digitalclassicist.org/Citations_with_CTS_and_Microformats>.

A working example of microformatted data that will be detected by this extension in contained in the file example_snippet.html

To use these user scripts with Operator, you must use Options->User Scripts to add them to Operator. After adding them, restart the browser.